Date: 10 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ministerio da Saude, Secretaria de Vigilancia em Saude,
Departamento de Vigilancia Epidemiologica, Coordenacao Geral de Doencas
Transmissiveis, 18 May 2006 [trans Mod.JW, edited]
<http://portal.saude.gov.br/portal/arquivos/pdf/nt_febreamarela.pdf>

TECHNICAL NOTE No. 07/2006/COVEV/CGDT/DEVEP/SVS/MS
Subject: Report on the epidemiological situation of Yellow Fever in Brazil
in 2006
Brasilia, 18 May 2006.
Situation in 2006.
-------------------
Up to epidemiological week 19/2006 [7 - 13 May 2006] 2 cases of yellow
fever, both fatal, were confirmed in the municipalities of Iranduba
(Amazonas state) & Nova Ubirata (Mato Grosso state).
During the same period, deaths in monkeys were reported from 2 states:
Tocantins, in the municipalities of Porto Nacional & Piraque, April 2006;
and Rio Grande do Sul, in the municipalities of Santo Antonio das Missoes &
Sao Nicolau in Feb 2006, and in the municipality of Joia, in May
2006. All were investigated, but due to logistical difficulties it was not
possible to collect adequate samples from all cases.
The epizootic in Joia is worrying, because the municipality is outside the
area of transition for YF, and therefore routine vaccination is not done
there. However, vaccination is planned for this and all other areas with
"epizootic rumors".
[See map at <http://www.fallingrain.com/world/BR/23/Joia.html> - Mod.JW]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
